Data Strategist		Droga5		Greater New York City Area		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>Droga5 is looking for a Data Strategist who can navigate between working closely with internal teams as well as clients to distill and analyze various forms of data (social, web, syndicated, etc.)  into actionable insights. </p><p>  </p><p>The ideal candidate would be someone who is passionate about using data to inform the  creation of better connections for consumers and to improve bottom line business results. Our NYC office is in need of a strong candidate that can take direction and learn quickly, while imparting their knowledge and expertise throughout the organization. </p><p>  </p><p>For the right person this role offers the chance to work with top tier clients (B2B, B2C,etc.), impact experiences that touch millions, be involved with award winning work and experience a great company culture.  </p><p></p><p>Responsibilities: </p><ul><li>Find new methods to optimize digital business through analytics and data </li><li>Manage the creation and distribution of detailed dashboards and metrics to the team </li><li>Produce detailed analytics requirements and specs for new initiatives and site / product launches </li><li>Develop tracking and data collection strategy to support business objectives (Goals, Objectives and KPI’s) </li><li>Evaluate potential vendors, products, and services to enable continued maturity of analytics tools and services </li><li>Monitor and measure launched products and feed learnings back into product development process </li><li>Act as a storyteller, translating complex analytical work into easily digested analysis and recommendations for client and account teams. </li><li>Dig into complex data to create quantitative marketing models, and tie them back to business results </li><li>Collect data from multiple sources including customer databases, ad servers, analytics packages, 3rd party services, and internal sources to create integrated dashboards and insights that can be used to drive decision making </li></ul><p> </p></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"></div>